@startuml
title Nobel Prize Laureates Autocomplete - Control Flow Component Diagram

skinparam componentStyle rectangle

package "Front-end (Public Directory)" {
    component [index.html] as HTML
    component [main.css] as CSS
    component [main.js] as MainJS

    HTML --> MainJS : loads script
    HTML --> CSS : applies styles
}

package "Back-end (Src Directory)" {
    component [server.js] as Server
    component [router.js] as Router
    component [handler.js] as Handler
    component [algorithm.js] as Algorithm
    database [data.json] as DataJSON

    Server --> Router : routes request
    Router --> Handler : delegates to handler
    Handler --> Algorithm : calls autocomplete
    Algorithm --> DataJSON : reads laureate data
}

package "Testing (Test Directory)" {
    component [qunit.html] as QUnit
    component [frontendTests.js] as FrontendTests
    component [backendTests.js] as BackendTests

    QUnit --> FrontendTests : runs tests
    BackendTests --> Algorithm : tests
}

interface "HTTP Request" as HTTPReq
interface "HTTP Response" as HTTPResp
interface "/search/:query API" as SearchAPI
interface "Static Files" as StaticFiles

Browser --> HTTPReq
HTTPReq --> Server : 1. User types in search
Server --> Router : 2. Forward request
Router --> Handler : 3. Route to handler
Handler --> StaticFiles : 3a. Serve static files
StaticFiles --> HTML : returns
Handler --> SearchAPI : 3b. Handle search request
SearchAPI --> Algorithm : 4. Execute autocomplete
Algorithm --> DataJSON : 5. Filter data
DataJSON --> Algorithm : 6. Return filtered results
Algorithm --> Handler : 7. Return suggestions
Handler --> HTTPResp : 8. Format response
HTTPResp --> MainJS : 9. Receive JSON data
MainJS --> HTML : 10. Update UI with suggestions

note right of MainJS
  Event-driven programming:
  - Listens for keystrokes
  - Async fetch to server
  - Updates suggestion list
end note

note right of Router
  RESTful API pattern:
  Routes requests based on URL
  /search/:query endpoint
end note

note right of Algorithm
  Core autocomplete logic:
  - Extracts data from JSON
  - Filters based on user input
  - Returns matching laureates
end note

@enduml
